Detailed Description

template<class T>
class fm::vector< T >

A STL vector with extra shortcuts to make the code more readable.

The most important shortcuts are 'contains', 'find' and 'erase'.

template<class T>
void fm::vector< T >::erase (  iterator  first,
iterator  last
)  [inline]
 

Removes a range of values from the list.

The range is determined as every value between and including the first value, up to the last value, but not including the last value.

Parameters:
first The first list value to remove.
last The last list value. This value will be kept.

You can use reserve zero values in order to clear the memory used by this list. This function is useful when optimizing.
